How the credit dispute process works!

Understanding the credit repair dispute process

Save this email to reference throughout your credit repair journey ~Contact.FirstName~, the Fair Credit Reporting Act (FCRA) gives consumers the ability to file disputes against erroneous, inaccurate, incomplete, or unverifiable information found on credit reports.

Contact Us

So when does the clock start?

Once the bureaus receive our request, they have 30 days to investigate and subsequently send a response letter with investigation results.

Learn More

Responses are sent directly to you.

Due to mail times, you can expect responses within 45-60 days.

Learn More

Sometimes the credit bureaus don't respond or use stall tactics. We are experts at dealing with this!

What if the Bureau(s) DONT respond?

This is not uncommon. One or more of the bureaus may fail to respond, or they may respond with a stall letter. If they do not respond in time, it can be argued that the items should be deleted in accordance with the Fair Credit Reporting Act's requirement for a proper investigation. But often it's not this simple.

Contact Us

These responses are extremely important.

They let you know if the disputed information was modified or removed.

They also help us dictate what our next steps are in the process.

What's the next move?

  • Our next move depends on which bureau responded and whether it's complete or incomplete investigation with proper verification.

  • If we are lucky, the bureau will have removed or modified incorrect items. If this is the case, we can continue with the credit rebuilding process.

  • We are very diligent in watching for any new inquiries that may have been added as well as any new adverse information (i.e., late payments).

  • We cannot stress enough how important it is for us to monitor your credit report on a regular basis when going through the credit disputes process. This is why we ask you to keep credit monitoring active through MyScoreIQ.

This process takes a great deal of patience and dedication. It's important not to get discouraged after a couple months pass without results.
